solution: SELECT count(*) FROM COUNTRIES;
answer: SELECT COUNT(CountryName) FROM countries;

solution: SELECT T1.FullName ,  T1.Id ,  count(*) FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id;
answer: SELECT T1.FullName, T2.ModelId, COUNT(T2.ModelId) FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN model_list AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.FullName

solution: SELECT T1.FullName ,  T1.Id ,  count(*) FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id;
answer: SELECT T1.FullName, T1.Id, COUNT(T3.ModelId) FROM car_makers AS T1 INNER JOIN model_list AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.Maker INNER JOIN model_list AS T3 ON T2.Maker = T3.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id

solution: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.horsepower ASC LIMIT 1;
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T2."MakeId" = T1."Id" ORDER BY T1.Horsepower LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.horsepower ASC LIMIT 1;
answer: SELECT cars_data.* FROM cars_data INNER JOIN car_names ON cars_data.Id = car_names.MakeId ORDER BY CAST(REPLACE(cars_data.Horsepower, 'hp', '') AS REAL) ASC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Weight < ( SELECT AVG(Weight) FROM cars_data )

solution: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)
answer: SELECT T2.Model FROM cars_data AS T1 JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId WHERE Weight < (SELECT AVG(Weight) FROM cars_data) AND T1.Id IN ( SELECT Id FROM cars_data );

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';
answer: SELECT T1."Make", T3.Maker FROM car_names AS T1 INNER JOIN cars_data AS T2 ON T1.MakeId = T2.Id INNER JOIN car_makers AS T3 ON T3."Maker" = T1."Make" WHERE T2.Year = 1970

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';
answer: SELECT T4.Maker FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId INNER JOIN model_list AS T3 ON T2.Model = T3.Model INNER JOIN car_makers AS T4 ON T3.Maker = T4.Id WHERE T1.Year = 1970

solution: SELECT T2.Make ,  T1.Year FROM CARS_DATA AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Year  =  (SELECT min(YEAR) FROM CARS_DATA);
answer: SELECT T2.Make, MIN(T1.Year) FROM cars_data AS T1 INNER JOIN car_names AS T2 ON T1.Id = T2.MakeId GROUP BY T2.Make

solution: SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN rankings AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id ORDER BY T2.tours DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T2.first_name, T2.country_code FROM rankings AS T1 INNER JOIN players AS T2 ON T2.player_id = T1.player_id ORDER BY T1.tours DESC LIMIT 1;

solution: SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN rankings AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id ORDER BY T2.tours DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT YEAR FROM matches GROUP BY YEAR ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT winner_name ,  winner_rank_points FROM matches GROUP BY winner_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T2.winner_name, T2.winner_rank_points FROM matches AS T1 INNER JOIN players AS T2 ON T1.winner_id = T2.player_id GROUP BY T2.player_id ORDER BY COUNT(T1.match_num) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT winner_name ,  winner_rank_points FROM matches GROUP BY winner_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT winner_name, SUM(winner_rank_points) FROM matches GROUP BY winner_name ORDER BY SUM(winner_rank_points) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT winner_name FROM matches WHERE tourney_name  =  'Australian Open' ORDER BY winner_rank_points DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.winner_name FROM matches AS T1 INNER JOIN players AS T2 ON T1.winner_id = T2.player_id WHERE T1.tourney_name = 'Australian Open' AND EXISTS ( SELECT 1 FROM matches AS T3 WHERE T3.winner_rank_points = ( SELECT MAX(winner_rank_points) FROM matches ) AND T3.tourney_name = 'Australian Open' )

solution: SELECT winner_name FROM matches WHERE tourney_name  =  'Australian Open' ORDER BY winner_rank_points DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T2.winner_name FROM matches AS T1 INNER JOIN players AS T2 ON T1.winner_id = T2.player_id WHERE T1.tourney_name = 'Australian Open' AND T2.name IS NOT NULL GROUP BY T2.name ORDER BY SUM(T2.winner_rank_points) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT winner_name ,  loser_name FROM matches ORDER BY minutes DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.winner_name, T1.loser_name FROM matches AS T1 INNER JOIN players AS T2 ON T1.loser_id = T2.player_id ORDER BY T1.minutes DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT winner_name ,  loser_name FROM matches ORDER BY minutes DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T2.winner_name, T1.loser_name FROM matches AS T1 INNER JOIN players AS T2 ON T1.winner_id = T2.player_id ORDER BY T1.minutes DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT T2.Language FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.Continent  =  "Asia" GROUP BY T2.Language ORDER BY COUNT (*) DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T2.Language FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.Continent = 'Asia' GROUP BY T2.Language ORDER BY COUNT(T2.Language) DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT T2.Language FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.GovernmentForm  =  "Republic" GROUP BY T2.Language HAVING COUNT(*)  =  1

solution: SELECT T1.Name ,  T1.Population FROM city AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.CountryCode  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" ORDER BY T1.Population DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.Name FROM city AS T1 INNER JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.CountryCode = T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language = 'English' ORDER BY T1.Population DESC LIMIT 1;

solution: SELECT T1.Name ,  T1.Population FROM city AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.CountryCode  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" ORDER BY T1.Population DESC LIMIT 1

solution: SELECT Name ,  Population ,  LifeExpectancy FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia" ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT T1.Name, T1.Population, T1.SurfaceArea FROM country AS T1 JOIN country AS T2 ON T2.Code = ( SELECT Code FROM country WHERE SurfaceArea = ( SELECT MAX(SurfaceArea) FROM country ) AND Continent = 'Asia' )

solution: SELECT Name ,  Population ,  LifeExpectancy FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia" ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 1
answer: SELECT Name, Population, LifeExpectancy FROM country WHERE Continent = "Asia" ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 1;

solution: SELECT avg(LifeExpectancy) FROM country WHERE Name NOT IN (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T")
answer: SELECT AVG(c.LifeExpectancy) FROM country c JOIN countrylanguage cl ON c.Code = cl.CountryCode WHERE c.Code NOT IN ('ABW') AND (cl.Language = 'English' OR cl.Percentage < 1.0)

solution: SELECT avg(LifeExpectancy) FROM country WHERE Name NOT IN (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T")
answer: SELECT AVG(LifeExpectancy) FROM country WHERE Code NOT IN ( SELECT CountryCode FROM countrylanguage WHERE Language = 'English' );

solution: SELECT sum(Population) FROM country WHERE Name NOT IN (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English")
answer: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Percentage < 1 THEN T1.Population ELSE 0 END) FROM country AS T1 LEFT JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.CountryCode

solution: SELECT sum(Population) FROM country WHERE Name NOT IN (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English")
answer: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.Code) FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language != 'English'

solution: SELECT T2.Language FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.HeadOfState  =  "Beatrix" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"

solution: SELECT T2.Language FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.HeadOfState  =  "Beatrix" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"

solution: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.Language) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE  IndepYear  <  1930 AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"
answer: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.Code) FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.IsOfficial = 'T' AND T1.IndepYear < 1930;

solution: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.Language) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE  IndepYear  <  1930 AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"
answer: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T2.Language) FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.IndepYear < 1930

solution: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE SurfaceArea  >  (SELECT min(SurfaceArea) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Europe")

solution: select distinct t3.name from country as t1 join countrylanguage as t2 on t1.code  =  t2.countrycode join city as t3 on t1.code  =  t3.countrycode where t2.isofficial  =  't' and t2.language  =  'chinese' and t1.continent  =  "asia"
answer: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 INNER JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code = T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.Continent = 'Asia' AND T2.Language = 'Chinese' AND T2.IsOfficial = 'T'

solution: SELECT DISTINCT T3.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode JOIN city AS T3 ON T1.Code  =  T3.CountryCode WHERE T2.IsOfficial  =  'T' AND T2.Language  =  'Chinese' AND T1.Continent  =  "Asia"
